abstract: While the presidential candidates argue about each other’s health plans, Michael Bloomberg’s ads have attacked the president over pre-existing conditions.
snippet: While the presidential candidates argue about each other’s health plans, Michael Bloomberg’s ads have attacked the president over pre-existing conditions.
lead_paragraph: It powered Democrats to recapture the House in the 2018 midterms: the fear that President Trump and Republicans would kill the Affordable Care Act and with it, protections for more than 50 million Americans with pre-existing medical conditions.

abstract: New York recycles only about a fifth of its trash, lagging behind other major cities and slowing its quest to reduce waste.
snippet: New York recycles only about a fifth of its trash, lagging behind other major cities and slowing its quest to reduce waste.
lead_paragraph: If you are a New Yorker and sort your recycling at home, as city law mandates, you probably wonder, as you rinse bottles and stack junk mail and scrub yogurt containers: Does all this effort make a difference?

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Wednesday, Jan. 29, 2020.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Wednesday, Jan. 29, 2020.
lead_paragraph: Because of an editing error, an article on Monday about the death of Kobe Bryant misspelled the surname of the chief medical examiner for Los Angeles County. He is Jonathan Lucas, not Luca.

abstract: Amy Klobuchar is still fighting to gain ground in Iowa's presidential caucuses that are now just days away.
snippet: Amy Klobuchar is still fighting to gain ground in Iowa's presidential caucuses that are now just days away.
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Amy Klobuchar is still fighting to gain ground in Iowa's presidential caucuses that are now just days away.
headline_main: Klobuchar Makes Quick Trip to Iowa in Midst of Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Klobuchar Makes Quick Trip to Iowa in Midst of Impeachment

abstract: Roughly 80 members of Congress, cabinet secretaries and administration officials will descend on the state to drive voter enthusiasm and make a show of force.
snippet: Roughly 80 members of Congress, cabinet secretaries and administration officials will descend on the state to drive voter enthusiasm and make a show of force.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Iowa caucuses on Monday will be a competitive race for only one party, the Democrats, but President Trump’s campaign does not see it that way.

abstract: Not everyone running for president is comfortable around dogs. But some 2020 contenders have made their canine companions into campaign stars.
snippet: Not everyone running for president is comfortable around dogs. But some 2020 contenders have made their canine companions into campaign stars.
lead_paragraph: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. — Last May, Senator Elizabeth Warren tweeted a photograph of a dog surrounded by the chewed-up detritus of what appeared to be some unfortunate household item. It was Bailey, her family’s adolescent golden retriever.

headline_main: When Your Best Surrogate Can’t Talk
headline_print_headline: Loyal, Playful Campaigners That Warm Instantly to Voters

abstract: The group, the Democratic Majority for Israel, will begin airing a negative campaign spot on Wednesday, as worries mount among moderate Democrats that Mr. Sanders could win the Iowa caucuses.
snippet: The group, the Democratic Majority for Israel, will begin airing a negative campaign spot on Wednesday, as worries mount among moderate Democrats that Mr. Sanders could win the Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A Democratic super PAC will begin airing attack ads in Iowa against Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont on Wednesday, marking the first time a Democratic organization has run a negative campaign spot targeting Mr. Sanders by name in either of his two primary campaigns.
